The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
Archives
 The City Diary
																																																		All India Minority Forum president Idris Ali, arrested on charges of spreading violence, rioting and arson in the city on November 21, was produced in Sealdah court on Thursday. His bail plea was rejected and his jail term extended till December 12. On Wednesday, Ali was produced before the chief judicial magistrate of Calcutta in a separate case on similar charges. He was remanded in jail custody till December 5. 																																																		A 59-year-old constable of the Calcutta police detective department killed himself on Thursday by jumping from a highrise, where he lived, in the Karaya police station area. Constable Tarachand Hansda threw himself from the 10th-floor balcony around 9am. No suicide note was found.																																																		A speeding minibus hit and injured Kameswar Jha, 70, a resident of Chitpur, late on Wednesday, at the Canning Street-Brabourne Road crossing.																																																		Rumki Dey, 16, took poison on Thursday afternoon at her Jagaddal home, on the citys northern fringes. No suicide note was found, but there was talk of a love affair behind the suicide. 
